				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.LFGzone.com" target="_blank">http://www.LFGzone.com</a>
<br />

<br />
I, for one, am pretty excited about this idea !
<br />

<br />
For some reason, nearly all my friends are taking a break from EQ.  This includes the new friends I made when LDON first came out.  Folks have just gone.
<br />

<br />
What I'd like to do most is get some high risk LDONs going, but this is nearly impossible with strangers.  And normal risk seem to be an excuse for everyone to run around like idiots each soloing their own mob; which isn't an adventure; it's a joke.
<br />

<br />
So I spend much of my time two-boxing my cleric or fishing or watching TV while LFG.  Been this way for the past month.
<br />

<br />
If I wasn't trying to save money, I'd quit EQ altogether and just go out partying all the time.
<br />

<br />
I'll definitely check out the site.  Thanks.
<br />

<br />
Arclan Cirel, 65 Paladin
<br />
Tallor, 65 Cleric
<br />

<br />
(edit) Just logged into the site and created a hunt.  Awesome site but it definitely needs refinement.  Submitted feedback requesting:  
<br />
1.  Need ability to edit created hunts, and I don't see an Edit link
<br />
2.  Need a box for AA, not just character level.  AAs make a big difference.
<br />
3.  The text box for description needs to be a full text field, allowing the group-leader to enter paragraphs of information.  It seems currently truncated at 244 characters which isn't enough.
<br />
4.  Each person signing up needs a place to add comments.
<br />

<br />

<br />
**********************************************
<br />
Also submitted following idea:
<br />

<br />
Have you considered adding a player-ranking or feedback system?  I.e., players who signed up together can rate each other on:
<br />

<br />
1. promptness, no-show, etc.
<br />
2. play skill, maturity level, etc.
<br />

<br />
I realize the 2nd item is a touchy one.
<br />

<br />
If I sign up for a few groups and the folks either don't show or are idiots then I would not be inclined to use the site further.
<br />

<br />
For example, lets say I start a hunt and someone signs up.  I can click on that person's name and read any feedback folks who played with that person have left.  And perhaps also read any feedback that player left for the other person.
<br />

<br />
Kinda complicated, messy stuff, though.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
