				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We put a lot of thought into your ideas, and although we had considered a few of them already, I think your post allowed us to go back and revisit our previous decisions.
<br />

<br />
1.  We are open to the idea of editing created hunts, but we will not allow posters to edit the time or place of the hunt.  We feel that if you have people signed up for your hunt it would not be fair to change the location, time, and/or other attributes.  However, there are some options we are currently looking at making available.
<br />
2.  The AA box is something that we may add in the near future, or we may solve this problem by taking into account your suggestion part 1 number 4.  People who wish to join a hunt WILL have the ability to add text that will be linked to their character details.  An excellent idea that will also allow them to add details about their AA points.
<br />
3.  The text field for the group-leader / organizer will be extended very soon, probably by the end of this weekend.  After seeing your suggestion and the hunt you posted we realize the need for an extended number of characters.
<br />
4.  A comments field will be added to the site.  It may also substitute for the ability to enter in AA points.
<br />

<br />
Next suggestions . . .
<br />
1.  We considered the ability to rank players and allow feedback based on a performance level, but it wasn't in the scope of our initial launch date.  While we feel like a rating system could be very beneficial, we also realize that systems such as these can be abused.  A ranking system may be something we will add, but not in the near future.
<br />

<br />
I would like to say that membership at the site is increasing everyday, although we still don't have very large numbers of people signed up.  It will take a while to really get things rolling but I encourage people to at least visit us and bookmark and check back often.
<br />
Keep in mind that we will be expanding the site to include LFG tools for CoH, and other upcoming titles such as WoW, EQII, and MoX.
<br />

<br />
Thanks again for the wonderful feedback, you have truly helped us to better our site and make it more user friendly and useful.
<br />

<br />
-Nate
<br />
LFGzone.com</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
